The paper deals with algorithms for directed planar graphs, which are commonly studied in computational geometry (cs.CG). The problem of maximum flow is a classic topic in algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), and the paper presents a new algorithm for this problem. The use of arc capacities suggests a connection to network optimization (cs.NA). Finally, the problem of finding maximum flow can also be formulated as a linear programming problem, which falls under discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
